{
  "doc_id": "37248",
  "text": "Eggs are an important food source for balanced nutrition in humans. Polyunsaturated fatty acids (PUFAs) content is an important nutrition index of eggs. N-6 and n-3 PUFAs are essential fatty acids (FAs) for vertebrates. Linoleic Acid (LA) and Arachidonic Acid (ARA) are n-6 PUFAs, while Alpha-linolenic Acid (ALA), Eicosapentaenoic Acid (EPA), and Docosahexaenoic Acid (DHA) belong to n-3 PUFAs. N-6 and n-3 PUFAs play important parts in growth, development, and reproduction, because they are closely related to many diseases, such as inflammation [CITATION_1] , mood disorders [CITATION_2] , neurodevelopment problems, cardiovascular disease, and cancer [CITATION_3] ).",
